/* STDLIB/iii/katabasis/introspection.iii -- THE SELF-EXAMINATION: the faculty
 * III inherits to know itself WHOLE, and to refuse to name itself when it is not.
 *
 * The katabasis descent judges admissions (isa_admit), rewrite-law and
 * vocabulary consent (nomos_consent I/II), and holds the constitution root
 * (autognosis).  This organ is the descent's floor: III's ability to EXAMINE
 * ITSELF -- not a probe run against an organ from outside, but a SYSTEMWIDE
 * TRAIT the organism carries.  One faculty walks every registered organ,
 * re-derives its truth from scratch with THIS faculty's own independent logic
 * (the two-path law: the examiner never trusts the examined's own arithmetic),
 * and folds the whole into a VITALITY ROOT -- a single u64 that is nonzero iff
 * III examined itself and found itself coherent.  A sick organ collapses the
 * vitality to 0, exactly as an incoherent constitution collapses autognosis_root.
 *
 * There are no per-organ verification files.  Verification is intrinsic: to be
 * a registered organ of III is to be examinable HERE.  New organs join by
 * exposing an identity and their operational surface (they already do); the
 * systemwide reach grows as the roster grows.
 *
 * THE ROSTER (index -> organ; fault codes = base + arm, so a nonzero verdict
 * LOCATES the organ and the failing invariant):
 *   0  autognosis  (100+)  the constitution's coherence + root
 *   1  autophasis  (200+)  the pressed discovery, re-hunted from the universe
 *   2  synapse     (300+)  the constitution-pinned wire, frames + refusals
 *   3  admix       (400+)  the self-deriving diffuser, proven + measured
 *
 * NIH: composes the sealed organs it examines; pure integer forms otherwise.
 * Hexad: kind_essence.  Ring R0. */
module katabasis_introspection

/* ---- autognosis (the constitution) ---- */
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn autognosis_coherent() -> u32 from "autognosis.iii"
extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn autognosis_root() -> u64 from "autognosis.iii"
